iam Bowen Rowlands]]\n  |votes      = 5,233\n  |percentage = 61.5\n  |change     = +11.4\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Liberal Unionist Party\n  |candidate  = William Jones<ref>{{cite news|title=How Mr W Jones Holds His Meetings|url=http://newspapers.library.wales/view/3723466/3723472|accessdate=21 November 2017|newspaper=South Wales Daily News|date=11 Jul 1892|page=6}}</ref>\n  |votes      = 3,270\n  |percentage = 38.5\n  |change     = -11.4\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n  |votes      = 1,963\n  |percentage = 23.0\n  |change     = +22.8\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n  |votes      = 8,503\n  |percentage = 64.6\n  |change     = -4.4\n}}\n{{Election box registered electors|\n  |reg. electors = 13,155\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n  |winner     = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |swing      = +11.4\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Elections in the 1880s===\n{{Election box begin|title=[[1886 United Kingdom general election|General election 1886]]: Cardiganshire<ref name=\"Craig, F. W. S. 1885-1918\"/>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[William Bowen Rowlands]]\n  |votes      = 4,252\n  |percentage = 50.1\n  |change     = -12.0\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Liberal Unionist Party\n  |candidate  = [[David Davies (industrialist)|David Davies]]\n  |votes      = 4,243\n  |percentage = 49.9\n  |change     = +12.0\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n  |votes      = 9\n  |percentage = 0.2\n  |change     = -24.0\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n  |votes      = 8,495\n  |percentage = 69.0\n  |change     = -9.1\n}}\n{{Election box registered electors|\n  |reg. electors = 12,308\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n  |winner     = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |swing      = -12.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n[[File:David_Davies_industrialist.jpg|thumb|120px|Davies]]\n{{Election box begin|title=[[1885 United Kingdom general election|General election 1885]]: Cardiganshire <ref name=\"Craig, F. W. S. 1885-1918\"/><ref name=\"ReferenceLYB07\">The Liberal Year Book, 1907</ref><ref>Debrett's House of Commons & Judicial Bench, 1886</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[David Davies (industrialist)|David Davies]]\n  |votes      = 5,967\n  |percentage = 62.1\n  |change     = +2.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[Matthew Vaughan-Davies, 1st Baron Ystwyth|Matthew Vaughan-Davies]]\n  |votes      = 3,644\n  |percentage = 37.9\n  |change     = -2.1\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n  |votes      = 2,323\n  |percentage = 24.2\n  |change     = +4.2\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n  |votes      = 9,611\n  |percentage = 78.1\n  |change     = -4.1\n}}\n{{Election box registered electors|\n  |reg. electors = 12,308\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n  |winner     = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |swing      = +2.1\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n{{Election box begin|title=[[1880 United Kingdom general election|General election 1880]]: Cardiganshire <ref name=\"craig1832\">{{cite book|editor1-last=Craig|editor1-first=F. W. S.|editor-link=F. W. S. Craig|title=British Parliamentary Election Results 1832-1885|date=1977|publisher=Macmillan Press|location=London|isbn=978-1-349-02349-3|edition=1st|type=e-book}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[Lewis Pugh Pugh]]\n  |votes      = 2,406\n  |percentage = 60.0\n  |change     = +13.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      =Conservative Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[Thomas Edward Lloyd]]\n  |votes      = 1,605\n  |percentage = 40.0\n  |change     = -13.1\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n  |votes      = 801\n  |percentage = 20.0\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n  |votes      = 4,011\n  |percentage = 82.2\n  |change     = +3.7\n}}\n{{E